html(lang="en")
    head
        title Image Search Abstraction Layer
        link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css")

    body
        div(class="container")
            h1(class="header") Image Search Abstraction Layer
            br
            
            blockquote
                p User stories:
                ul
                    li 1) I can get the image URLs, alt text and page urls for a set of images relating to a given search string.
                    li 2) I can paginate through the responses by adding a ?offset=2 parameter to the URL.
                    li 3) I can get a list of the most recently submitted search strings.
            br

            h3 Example usage:
            code #{host}/api/imagesearch/lolcats%20funny?offset=10
            a(href="api/imagesearch/lolcats%20funny?offset=10") [Show in browser]
            br

            code #{host}/api/latest/imagesearch
            a(href="api/latest/imagesearch") [Show in browser]
            br
            br

            a(href=home) More freeCodeCamp apps